%N A397232 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} (-1)^(k+1) * AH(2*k,4)/k, where AH(k,4) = A120296(k)/A334585(k) is the k-th alternating harmonic (or skew-harmonic) number of order 4.
%H A397232 Cornel Ioan Vălean, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-21262-8">More (Almost) Impossible Integrals, Sums, and Series</a>, Springer Cham, 2023. See section 4.22, p. 426.
%H A397232 <a href="/index/Ha#harmonic">Index entries for sequences related to harmonic numbers</a>.
%F A397232 Equals 15*zeta(5)/4 + 3*zeta(2)*zeta(3)/128 +7*log(2)*zeta(4)/128 + Pi^5/192 - Pi^3*G/16 - Pi*polyGamma(3, 1/4)/1536, where G is Catalan's constant (A006752), and polyGamma(3, 1/4) = psi'''(1/4) is the third derivative of the digamma function at 1/4 (A390074).
%e A397232 0.647376089029579300423468267456825918600070549625977...
%t A397232 RealDigits[15*Zeta[5]/4 + 3*Zeta[2]*Zeta[3]/128 +7*Log[2]*Zeta[4]/128 + + Pi^5/192 - Pi^3*Catalan/16 - Pi*PolyGamma[3, 1/4]/1536, 10, 120][[1]]
%o A397232 (PARI) 15*zeta(5)/4 + 3*zeta(2)*zeta(3)/128 +7*log(2)*zeta(4)/128 + Pi^5/192 - Pi^3*Catalan/16 - Pi*psi'''(1/4)/1536
